[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering logging structure**\n\nI'm thinking about formats for the request log. I could create a custom `RequestLog.Writer`, which might mean needing a public top-level test class too. There’s a thought about having a dedicated class for each `CustomRequestLog`. In the existing `JettyTests`, I wonder if there’s already a custom request we could use. Maybe adding a `CustomRequestLogTest` file would be good, along with a helper for any duplicated ports.\n\n**Examining test conflicts**\n\nI’m thinking about whether `BeforeAll` can lead to test conflicts. JUnit might run tests sequentially, so using `Server(0)` and retrieving the local port after starting it sounds safer. Existing setups use a fixed port, which could work, but for a new class, I should definitely go with `Server(0)`. I might need to use `ServerConnector` for API access to that port. Jetty’s `getURI` method seems useful, especially for handling requests. There’s also a question about needing to close the `HttpClient` in Java 21—I believe it implements `AutoCloseable`, but it may not require it in this case.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0dda3a3c8a769bfe016a29ff12f43c8194b0b5221a63e229b8\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKf8n7cA4OcJ01swyTef9g14ZrzskGqAn_mf7UBheCIE9C5vu2BESiDhSJ5Tao9zDHxEwvOYen5QjOvBTF8mvedTBJ20y0VjEdzvLXzpat10pxood7VCtkeu98SwCQqWjlJjcmi5n_rGCVIMfYcamju1ZjYKFuO6Jb45s0x13ER4cd60NDFMtSC6RsBlm_ZJUTQ-jjI3fZ06-mDLNQa8-YsRQRWBY9kq7Wxe2xN1H8G3uhZeLeQLgQUyLaz7hP7_bCYDOV5qfqKuA7sb0Z9mF0EYTtWn19j2UymN37eOW2CxeXtAYsShQQVZWmO-XFFuPZBtqh-dIUNcCsoQTJpHYJSTJtLmw4UsWBAzP7RII4H1YJloWj5VL5gpCAOtbLB5T3-PaBQTpqvWlmX4GV5f_PuMRbg4bPcs1x2aCk34E6o_69qzxMyUIQflkVJic4yASGzP-4OTVhK9RIALIBzFPDQ9d1bdzbm_a21gvK8JRMOwIYad4WOJcAa2l8O32pp1OpKcI11BDtrmgmNKksY8JYdzUjOxfrte9RDdQjZ2cZnY7UvDhIHMheBQgWDZuqibXYtCPMLFfmas3tU_eb9S-xGoD2tos54c2DnKFHClxIg895yP7MmbkR1FibBr5LDvOoy